## Traps ‚Äî corrected from prior session

- **TrustPosture canonical names (CORRECTED).** Previous notes said `DELEGATED / CONTINUOUS_INSIGHT / SHARED_PLANNING / PSEUDO_AGENT` are canonical. They are **aliases**. Canonical names from `src/kailash/trust/posture/postures.py`:
  - `AUTONOMOUS` (level 5) ‚Äî alias `DELEGATED`
  - `DELEGATING` (level 4) ‚Äî alias `CONTINUOUS_INSIGHT`
  - `SUPERVISED` (level 3) ‚Äî alias `SHARED_PLANNING`
  - `TOOL` (level 2) ‚Äî no alias (was `HUMAN_DECIDES` in a long-removed surface)
  - `PSEUDO` (level 1) ‚Äî alias `PSEUDO_AGENT`
  Legacy names that raise `AttributeError`: `FULL_AUTONOMY`, `HUMAN_DECIDES`, `BLOCKED`, `ASSISTED`.
  Semantic mapping when reading old tests: `FULL_AUTONOMY ‚Üí AUTONOMOUS`, `HUMAN_DECIDES ‚Üí TOOL` (follow the `approval_required` branch in `TrustPostureMapper`, not the "denied" branch), `BLOCKED ‚Üí PSEUDO`, `ASSISTED ‚Üí SUPERVISED`.

- **`asyncio` in `__del__` is BLOCKED** (`rules/patterns.md` ¬ß Async Resource Cleanup). `DataFlow.__del__` previously routed through `async_safe_run` which spawned a new event loop thread that itself called `logger.debug()` during selector init ‚Äî deadlock on the logging root lock when the finalizer fired from inside logging machinery (GC during `logger.isEnabledFor`). Fix: `__del__` emits `ResourceWarning` only; cleanup via `await db.close_async()` or `with` ctx. **Do not restore async cleanup in `__del__`** under any circumstance.

- `extra={"name": ...}` in `logger.*` calls ‚Üí runtime `KeyError`. `name` is a reserved LogRecord attribute (see commit `fa7e1872`). Same class: `msg`, `message`, `module`, `filename`, `pathname`, `levelname`, `lineno`, `funcName`, `created`, `thread`, `processName`, `args`, `exc_info`, `stack_info`, `asctime`.

- `async def test_x(...)` that calls sync `LocalRuntime.execute(...)` deadlocks. Use `AsyncLocalRuntime` + `await runtime.execute_workflow_async(...)`.

- Pre-commit auto-stash loops when hooks rewrite the tree. Use `git -c core.hooksPath=/dev/null commit ‚Ä¶` and document the bypass per `rules/git.md` ¬ß Pre-Commit Hook Workarounds. `--no-verify` is BLOCKED.

- **DataFlow worktree pre-commit tries to run pytest against `.venv/bin/python` inside the worktree**, which doesn't exist (worktree shares main's venv). Pre-commit hook needs teaching to resolve to the main repo's venv. Until then, worktree commits use the `core.hooksPath=/dev/null` bypass.

